reviewText: One of the most entertaining classic movies I have ever seen. Uniquely hilarious! However, the video quality is only comparable to watching it on VHS. Having said that, this movie is not available through TCM where even their DVD-R, made on demand movies are of excellent viewing quality, so it is worth having until then.

OMG, people. Oh. My. God.
This movie is effed up. FABULOUS. Tap-dancing on a streamliner train. George Burns and Gracie Allen in black face.
American college kids put into a eugenics program in 1936.
What part of this do you not understand?
OMG.
